Step 2 – Sign the Hash

Alice encrypts only the hash using her Private Key.

Hash

↓

Alice's Private Key

↓

Digital Signature

Notice:

The message itself is not encrypted.

Only its hash is signed.

Step 3 – Send

Alice sends:

Message
Digital Signature

to Bob.

Step 4 – Verification

Bob:

Hashes the received message.
Uses Alice's Public Key to verify the signature.

If both hashes match:

✅ Message is authentic.

✅ Message has not been modified.

Why Sign the Hash Instead of the Entire File?

Imagine signing:

50 GB Movie

Instead of:

256-bit Hash

Signing the hash is much faster while still guaranteeing integrity.

