Why Doesn't HTTPS Use RSA for Everything?

RSA is secure but slow.

Encrypting:

10 GB Video

using RSA would be inefficient.

Instead:

RSA/ECC securely exchanges the AES Session Key.
AES encrypts all application data.

This provides both:

Security
Performance
